<p class='question'>1. Print out the names of the atomic elements in alphabetical order.</p>

  <% @elements.each do |e| %> &nbsp
  <h6><li style="color: red"><%= e.name %></li></h6>
  <% end %>


<p class='question'>2. Print out the name for the element with number of 27.</p>

  <% @elements.each do %> &nbsp
  <% e = Element.find_by(number: 27) %>
  <li style="color: red"><%= e.name %></li>
  <% break %>
  <% end %>
<br>
<p class='question'>3. Print the name of the element with the lowest melting point.</p>

  <% @elements.each do %> &nbsp
  <% e = Element.order(:melting_point).first %>
  <li style="color: red"><%= e.name %></li>
  <% break %>
  <% end %>
<br>


<p class='question'>4. Print the name of the element with the highest melting point. Hint: you'll need to filter out the NULL records with <code>where("melting_point is not null")</code>.</p>

  <% @elements.each do %> &nbsp
  <% e = Element.order(:melting_point).reverse_order.first %>
  <li style="color: red"><%= e.name %></li>
  <% break %>
  <% end %>
<br>

<p class='question'>5. Print out all the element names that end with the letters ium.  (e.g. Calcium)</p>


  <% Element.where("name like ?", "%ium").each do |e| %>
    <li style="color: red"><%= e.name %></li>
  <% end %>


<p class='question'>6. Print out the name and number for each of the noble gases.  Look in the <code>category</code> field to find the noble gases.</p>

  <% Element.where(category: "noble gases").each do |e| %>
  <li style="color: red"><%= e.name %> &nbsp
  <%= e.number %></li>
  <% end %>
<br>

<p class='question'>7. Print out the symbols for the alkali metals, sorted alphabetically.  Look in the <code>category</code> field to find the alkali metals.</p>
  <% Element.order(:symbol).where(category: "alkali metals").each do |e| %>
  <li style="color: red"><%= e.symbol %></li> 
  <% end %>

<br>

<p class='question'>8. Print out element names with atomic number of 10 or below.  Example less-than method call: <code>where("year &lt; 1998")</code></p>

  <% Element.where("number < 11").each do |e| %>
  <li style="color: red"><%= e.name %></li>
  <% end %>
<br>  

